Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper proposes a novel scheme based on superposition coding to reduce inter-node communication load during the Shuffle phase. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is likely because the paper deals with a distributed computing system in which worker nodes are connected over a shared wireless channel. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is likely because the paper proposes a Map-Shuffle-Reduce protocol for collaborative processing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible because the paper deals with wireless communication systems and proposes a scheme to improve their performance. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible because the paper deals with processing a data set, which could potentially include multimedia data.
